    <name>
      <text>Computing determinants of matrix given 3 vectors in R^3</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Let \(u_1= ({@a@}, {@b@}, {@c@}), \, u_2=({@d@}, {@e@}, {@f@}), \, u_3=({@g@}, {@h@}, {@i@})\).</p>
<p>Find the volume \(V(S)\) of the parallelepiped \(S\) in \(\mathbb{R}^3\) determined by the three vectors.</p>
<br>a) Write the three vectors in matrix form \(A=\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>
<p>b) Compute the determinant of \(A\) and use it to find the volume of the parallelepiped \( V(S)=\)  [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p><h3>Worked Solution</h3></p>
<p>We let \(A\) be the matrix of the three vectors and find the determinant of \(A\)</p>
<p>\(A={@A@}\). The matrix \(A\) can also be represented like this, \( {@transpose(A)@}\).</p>
<p>
\(
\begin{align}
V(S) &= | det(A)| \\
       &= |{@+a@} \cdot {@submatrix1@} - {@b@} \cdot {@submatrix2@} + {@c@} \cdot {@submatrix3@}| \\
       &= |{@a*determinant(submatrix1)@}-{@b*determinant(submatrix2)@}+{@c*determinant(submatrix3)@}| \\    
            &={@ta2@}   \\
          V(S) &= {@ta2@}  \text{ cubic units}.

\end{align}
\)
</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
